Poland is planning to send 74 main battle tanks to Ukraine in order to strengthen the country's ability to hold off against a possible Russian offensive. Warsaw will be providing 14 German-made Leopard 2s and 60 renovated tanks inherited from the Soviet Union, the country announced on Friday. Polish prime minister Mateusz Morawiecki told Canada’s CTV News: "If we don't want Ukraine to be defeated, we have to be very much open and brave in supporting Ukraine. "These were the arguments and also if Ukraine, God forbid, fails in defending their sovereignty and freedom, it would mean only the first step in the Kremlin's mad strategy to rebuild the Russian Empire from the past. “ PLEASE FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...